Serves: 2-4, depending on the size of the glassesIngredients:375ml (1 cups) milk x 385g can condensed milk2.5ml ( tsp) nutmeg2.5ml ( tsp) ground cinnamon125ml ( cup) Amarula liqueurMethod:1) Bring the milk, condensed milk and spices to a gentle boil in a pan on the stove. Remove from the heat, add the liqueur and stir well.2) Serve warm with an extra sprinkling of nutmeg and cinnamon; or cool completely and serve in tall glasses with lots of ice and a sprinkling of extra spice.This is one of many tasty recipes you'll find in the new 'Sunday Times Food Weekly Cookbook 4'.